main event: A witness spotted a white, rectangular object with blinking lights in the sky over Winter Park, Florida in May 1966.
interesting points: The object was approximately 75 feet in the air and drifted back and forth at the same height.
The object rapidly picked up speed, going from a slow start to disappearing within 60-70 seconds.
The witness, who had a private pilot's license with 3,000 hours of flying time, reported the sighting as highly reliable.
The sighting occurred on a clear night with moderate winds and some cloud cover.
No other corroborating witnesses or physical evidence is mentioned in the report.
sighted object: a white, rectangular object with blinking lights
witnesses: a private pilot with approximately 3,000 hours of flying time
photographs: no photographs included in the report
